    <item>
      <title>The Thief’s Story</title>
      <link>https://stories.muthu.co/posts/ruskin-the-thiefs-story/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://stories.muthu.co/posts/ruskin-the-thiefs-story/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;I was still a thief when I met Romi. I was only fifteen, but I was good at it. Romi was watching a wrestling match when I walked up to him. He looked like he was about twenty-five, and he seemed friendly and easy to trick. I thought I could easily become his friend.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;figure class=&#34;&#34;&gt;&#xA;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;img-container&#34; style=&#34;--w: 1024; --h: 673;&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;img loading=&#34;lazy&#34; alt=&#34;A skinny, young boy (Hari Singh), no older than 15, with a mischievous grin and close-cropped, dusty brown hair, approaches a slightly older man (Romi), maybe 25, with a lean build and kind eyes. Romi is captivated by a wrestling match in the foreground. The wrestling ring is a makeshift pit in a dusty, vibrant Indian market, with two powerfully built wrestlers grappling in a cloud of sweat and dust, their oiled bodies glistening under the harsh midday sun. The scene is alive with the cacophony of market sounds and a riot of colors: saffron robes, turquoise textiles, and earthen browns. Sunlight creates deep shadows, highlighting the texture of the rough-hewn wooden fence surrounding the ring and the animated faces in the crowd. Watercolor illustration with soft blending and natural flow, capturing the vibrant energy of India.&#34; src=&#34;https://stories.muthu.co/posts/images/image_ruskin-the-thiefs-story0.png&#34; width=&#34;1024&#34; height=&#34;673&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;    &#xA;&lt;/figure&gt;&#xA;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>The Tunnel</title>
      <link>https://stories.muthu.co/posts/ruskin-the-tunnel/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://stories.muthu.co/posts/ruskin-the-tunnel/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;figure class=&#34;&#34;&gt;&#xA;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;img-container&#34; style=&#34;--w: 1024; --h: 680;&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;img loading=&#34;lazy&#34; alt=&#34;A young boy, Suraj, stands near weathered train tracks disappearing into the inky maw of a dark tunnel entrance deep within a lush, vibrant green jungle. The late afternoon sun casts long, dappled shadows through the dense foliage. The air above the tracks shimmers with intense heat haze, distorting the distant view. A rusty bicycle, its tires slightly deflated, leans against the gnarled roots of a nearby banyan tree. Suraj is barefoot, wearing a faded blue shirt and brown shorts, his face etched with a mixture of excitement and trepidation. Watercolor style, soft blending, natural flow.&#34; src=&#34;https://stories.muthu.co/posts/images/image_ruskin-the-tunnel0.png&#34; width=&#34;1024&#34; height=&#34;680&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;    &#xA;&lt;/figure&gt;&#xA;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>The Wind on Haunted Hill</title>
      <link>https://stories.muthu.co/posts/ruskin-the-wind-on-haunted-hill/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://stories.muthu.co/posts/ruskin-the-wind-on-haunted-hill/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Whoosh, whoosh, whoosh, sang the wind as it rushed down from the snowy mountains. It zoomed over the hills, humming and whistling through the tall trees. Haunted Hill didn&amp;rsquo;t have much to stop the wind – just some small trees and bushes, and the broken walls of an old town.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;figure class=&#34;&#34;&gt;&#xA;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;img-container&#34; style=&#34;--w: 682; --h: 1024;&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;img loading=&#34;lazy&#34; alt=&#34;Watercolor illustration of Usha, Suresh, and Binya on a windy hilltop village. They are securing vibrant, patched clothes – a faded blue shirt, a red and yellow sari – to a crumbling stone wall with jagged-edged rocks. Usha has dark, windblown hair framing a face with rosy cheeks, her brow furrowed in concentration. Suresh is younger and smaller, clutching a stone tightly, his eyes wide with exertion. Binya is slightly older than Usha, her hands deftly pinning a colorful cloth, a serene expression on her face despite the harsh wind. In the background, a distant, dilapidated town sits atop another hill, partially obscured by blowing wind and a hazy, grey sky tinged with a touch of lavender. The watercolor effect should emphasize the texture of the stone, the wind&amp;rsquo;s movement through the clothing, and the soft, diffused light typical of a windy day. The overall tone is one of resilience and quiet determination, rendered with delicate watercolor washes.&#34; src=&#34;https://stories.muthu.co/posts/images/image_ruskin-the-wind-on-haunted-hill0.png&#34; width=&#34;682&#34; height=&#34;1024&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;    &#xA;&lt;/figure&gt;&#xA;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Those Three Bears</title>
      <link>https://stories.muthu.co/posts/ruskin-those-three-bears/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://stories.muthu.co/posts/ruskin-those-three-bears/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Most villages in the Himalaya mountains are in valleys. Valleys have little streams, some places to grow food, and they&amp;rsquo;re safe from the super cold winds that blow through the mountains in winter. The houses are usually built with big rocks and have slanted roofs made of stone, so the heavy rain can slide right off. When it&amp;rsquo;s sunny in the fall, you&amp;rsquo;ll often see pumpkins on the roofs, getting all nice and ripe in the sun.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Tiger My Friend</title>
      <link>https://stories.muthu.co/posts/ruskin-tiger-my-friend/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://stories.muthu.co/posts/ruskin-tiger-my-friend/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;figure class=&#34;&#34;&gt;&#xA;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;img-container&#34; style=&#34;--w: 766; --h: 1024;&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;img loading=&#34;lazy&#34; alt=&#34;Watercolor illustration of an old tiger with gold and yellow fur, streaked with mud and battle scars, walking purposefully through tall, dry grass near a misty swamp at sunset. Long shadows stretch from the tiger, highlighting the texture of its fur. The tiger&amp;rsquo;s tail, tipped with black, is just visible above the golden grass. Water lilies with delicate white and yellow petals float on the dark, still water. A faint orange glow reflects off the water, creating a warm, melancholic tone. The air is thick with humidity. Style: Soft watercolor with visible brushstrokes and color bleeding, capturing the raw texture of the environment.&#34; src=&#34;https://stories.muthu.co/posts/images/image_ruskin-tiger-my-friend0.png&#34; width=&#34;766&#34; height=&#34;1024&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;    &#xA;&lt;/figure&gt;&#xA;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Wild Fruit</title>
      <link>https://stories.muthu.co/posts/ruskin-wild-fruit/</link>
